This is my habit tracker console project. I followed the thecsharpacademy tutorial video on vs code
then moved in visual studio.
Features:
I added a tracker class out of main to call the static method on tracker.
The table in the db now has a name of the habit, date of habit, number of unit and unit of the habit.
User can choose what habit they will log, when it happened, for how long and what unit to measure the habit.

Challenges:
I tried to write unit tests for at least the return methods, but first, the return methods had so much going
on, user interface, getting input from user, and calculation. I ended up testing microsofts methods tryparse
which didnt make sense in the second place. I will come back to it, and make methods less coupled so they can
be tested.
